My credentials for this information is that I had anaphylactic reactions nearly every day, described the symptoms to my Dr & my gi Dr and it took them 5 years to notice it and refer me to an allergist (only after I told my Dr I was sure it was an allergy).

Anaphylaxis will actually look more like a panic attack than a movie version of an allergic reaction. A fairly unique symptom is an overwhelming feeling of impending doom. Other symptoms include confusion, numbness in hands & face, shortness of breath, stumbling, & fainting.

Just a PSA that most information about anaphylaxis online & in media is wrong. Anaphylaxis does not need to have any external visible symptoms. Anaphylaxis is a different kind of allergic reaction to hives & swelling. Hives & swelling my co-occur, but are distinct reactions.
